IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO FORGE ALLIANCES BETWEEN PROPERTY OWNERS, BUSINESS INTERESTS, RESIDENTS AND THE CITY OF ARLINGTON TO IMPROVE AND ENHANCE THE ECONOMIC VITALITY AND OVERALL ENVIRONMENT OF DOWNTOWN ARLINGTON.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO FORGE ALLIANCES BETWEEN PROPERTY OWNERS, BUSINESS INTERESTS, RESIDENTS AND THE CITY OF ARLINGTON TO IMPROVE AND ENHANCE THE ECONOMIC VITALITY AND OVERALL ENVIRONMENT OF DOWNTOWN ARLINGTON.
IRS990.Desc: Several new businesses opened, including new restaurants, retail and destination businesses. New residential developments continued under construction, including for sale residential. We consistently promoted Downtown Arlington and positively affected the overall perceptions about the downtown area, serving the economic interests of the city and its citizens. We expanded our social media presence, leveraged the use of our updated website with more businesses, and built strong support and branding for a new music festival. We also expanded our beautification efforts with increased litter patrol, and continued providing storefront grants to property owners.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Organization is exempt from federal income taxes under section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code (IRC) and has not been classified as a private foundation as defined in the IRC. Income generated from activities unrelated to DAMCs exempt purposes is subject to tax under IRC Section 511. DAMC had no unrelated business income for the year ended September 30, 2022. Accordingly, no provision has been made for federal income tax. GAAP requires the evaluation of tax positions taken in the course of preparing DAMCs tax returns and recognition of a tax liability (or asset) if DAMC has taken an uncertain position that more likely than not would not be sustained upon examination by the Internal Revenue Service. Management has analyzed the tax positions taken by DAMC, and has concluded that as of September 30, 2022, there are no uncertain tax positions taken or expected to be taken that would require recognition of a liability (or asset) or disclosure in the financial statements.
